docs.abstract: Handmade posters, reading “Authoritarian,” “Classist” and “Oligarch,” were plastered on the windows of a Bloomberg field office in Knoxville, Tenn.
docs.snippet: Handmade posters, reading “Authoritarian,” “Classist” and “Oligarch,” were plastered on the windows of a Bloomberg field office in Knoxville, Tenn.
docs.lead_paragraph: A field office for Michael R. Bloomberg’s presidential campaign in Knoxville, Tenn., was vandalized overnight, the latest in a series of vandalism incidents that prompted top campaign officials to blame Senator Bernie Sanders for the attacks.

headline.main: Bloomberg Campaign Blames Sanders Supporters Over Insults in Vandalism

docs.abstract: A day before the caucuses, the state party says volunteer and staff members at caucus sites are forbidden to talk to the news media.
docs.snippet: A day before the caucuses, the state party says volunteer and staff members at caucus sites are forbidden to talk to the news media.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — One day before the Nevada caucuses, the state Democratic Party has asked all caucus site leaders to sign a nondisclosure agreement preventing them from talking to the news media. State party officials began to present the agreements to site leaders Friday.

headline.main: Nevada Democrats Demand That Caucus Site Leaders Sign Nondisclosure Agreements
headline.print_headline: Site Leaders Asked to Sign Confidentiality Agreements

docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris is weighing an endorsement of Joseph R. Biden Jr., according to multiple Democratic officials familiar with her deliberations. Such a move could lift Mr. Biden’s campaign and perhaps do even more to enhance Ms. Harris’s chances of becoming vice president, but it could also anger her liberal base in California.

docs.abstract: The move by the group of young climate activists was another sign that left-wing advocacy organizations have increasingly coalesced around the Vermont senator’s candidacy.
docs.snippet: The move by the group of young climate activists was another sign that left-wing advocacy organizations have increasingly coalesced around the Vermont senator’s candidacy.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Sunrise Movement, the collection of young climate activists who have roiled Capitol Hill and the Democratic presidential primary,  announced on Thursday that it was endorsing Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, in another sign that left-wing advocacy groups have increasingly coalesced around his candidacy.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders’s Latest Endorsement: Sunrise Movement
headline.print_headline: Sanders Gets Endorsement Of Young Climate Group, Bolstering Left-Wing Ties

docs.abstract: Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar hit the 2020 campaign trail on Saturday during a break in the impeachment trial.

docs.lead_paragraph: MARSHALLTOWN, Iowa — Senators Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar dashed back to Iowa for a frenzied burst of campaigning on Saturday after a week in which they were confined to Washington for the impeachment trial of President Trump.

headline.main: ‘Good Not to Be In Washington’: Senators Return to Iowa for Burst of Campaigning
headline.print_headline: In Break From Impeachment Duties, 2020 Candidates Return to Campaigning
